texts.text: *Wince*

What? Who are you?
You dare interrupt our fight?
No matter! I will just have to deal with you first!
Not happening!

*Wince*
Pests, all of you!

Chi You, wake up!
Get that kid out of here!
Y-Yes...
>Chi You grabs the girl, clear a path through the demons and reaches the exit.
Why did you come to my aid...?
Those demons were not about to hold back. You could have died.
B-Because...
You helped us, so I wanted to return the favor...
>She exits the Aura Gate as she says that.
H-How can this be...?
She felt indebted to me after helping her just one time?
So pathetic and foolish... I simply do not understand...
I feel... Alive!
Ugh, so strong...!
I will just have to kill you first since you like to interrupt so much!
No, you have lost.

*Wince*
Brother!
Chi You, what happened to the kid?!
Do not worry. She has returned to her world.
You have become these humans' servant! Oh, how the mighty have fallen!
No, brother...
I have learned much during my time with them.

Arrrgh!
Silence!
*Grunt*
>Chi You and his brothers clash as a fierce battle unfolds.
>As they struggle, Chi You starts to gain the upper hand.

No...!
You are supposed to be weak!

What is this power?!
How are you so strong?!

Surprised?
So am I.
I did not know that my realization just now would grant me such strength.
What are you talking about?! What realization?!
The power to protect.
I will protect Gakuto from your blade and save the girl from becoming demon fodder.
This is the power Huang Di wielded while seeking to maintain peace in his lands!

The power to protect?!
Do not make me laugh!

Gakuto, he is strong.
You must aid me.
Yeah, let's do it!
>Gakuto joins Chi You and helps knock away the demon's weapon.

*Wince*
N-Nooo...

There!
Chi You, now!
*Roar*
>As Chi You roars, his weapon pierces the demon's body.
You scoffing at my remark is the reason you lost.
Today, you are defeated.
B-Brother...
>Chi You's brother disappears...
Phew. Finally...
>The Liberators begin to regroup just as Chi You's battle ends.
Gakuto, Chi You, thank goodness you're both okay.
The others all managed to safely make it out of here.
All that's left is to clean up the rest of these thugs.
Wait...
>Just as Chi You begins speaking, the fog begins to lift completely.
That was the last one it seems.
Liberators, you must go at once.
This place will not last much longer now that it has fulfilled its purpose.
Right. Let's get out of here.
Thanks, Chi You!
>As the Liberators leave, Gakuto remains.
How does it feel, Chi You...?
Fighting for someone's sake instead of your own?

Not bad...
Thank you, Gakuto.
You made me realize that there is value in protecting someone other than myself.
And we are now comrades in arms.
Stop right there! I never said that once even when I was still a merc!
How about we become otaku buddies instead?

Otaku? Buddies?
What is that...?
Okay, otaku buddies are...
How friends enjoy living in such a peaceful world!
Huang Di, you are there, are you not?
Ah, you sensed my presence...
I know that you are not one who simply lets things be as they are.
If I concluded that I must bring harm to these humans,
you would have stepped in to stop me.
You have always loved conflict. But when we last spoke, you were conflicted,
and you certainly could have made the decision to go to war.
However, I see that you have found a different answer.
That girl. She stood up to my brother after helping her just one time...
There was no way she could win. She could have died right there.
Even in a peaceful world, these humans are able to risk their lives for others.
That courage showed me what it truly means to live.
It was also when I knew that I had to protect those humans, including her,
and this strange power began coursing through my body.
You wielded this very power against me, did you not?
It is no wonder I could not defeat you.
If you managed to realize that much,
then you must understand why these humans wish to maintain peace in their world.
They do not wish to see their loves ones vanish before their eyes.
And if avoiding conflict is the solution, so be it, correct?
I understand your thinking now.
However, Huang Di, I will not stop fighting.
Good...
Those who seek peace must be met with those who seek war.
There are certainly those who are cowed by peace.
But I vow to not accrue power simply for the sake of becoming more powerful,
and to fight against what truly threatens this world.
Let us fight together while working to protect it.
But in the end, I seem to prefer conflict much more than peace.
I see...
On the other hand...
If no others like that appear, then I suppose it is not necessary to start a war.
Farewell, Huang Di.
The next time we meet, let us fight together to protect those that need protecting.
>Chi You vanishes as he finishes speaking...
My word...
I was hoping that he would open his eyes to the value of peace,
but to think that this is how everything would turn out. He is as invigorated as ever.
I will need to keep my guard up the next time we meet.
>A few days after the Aura Gate disappeared...

*Roar*
Shionyan!
Shionyan's shows really are the best!
You think so too, right, Newbie!
Yeah!
Shionyan!
You're finally starting to see why Shionyan's so great!
Whoa, Newbie's calling her name now! I'm not letting you win that easily!
I have to cheer as much as I can to make up for the time I lost!
Hey, does that mean you aren't always cheering as loudly as you can?
No, ma'am! Never! I am always cheering to the best of my abilities!

Good.
Keep cheering like your life depends on it.
Man, Shionyan's shows are as good as being on the battlefield...!
But this has something that the battlefield didn't.
This is something I want to protect. Something I want to fight for.
No, stop, or else she'll get mad again!

*Roar*
SHIONYAAAN!!!

*Sigh*
Being an otaku's the best part of living in a peaceful world!
